records.Name: Asian Americans United
records.Description: The AAU Summer Program is a 6-week leadership program for high school youth. The program is designed to develop the leadership potential, cultural identities, and social justice consciousness of youths and campers, so that they can make a positive difference and create change in their communities. Serving ESL and Asian Youth; citywide.

records.Name: Bartram's Garden
records.Description: The Bartram?s Garden summer youth intern program comprises of an experience working alongside either Sankofa Community Farm or the Roots Tree Crew. Sankofa interns study all aspects of farming and food sovereignty while also focusing on leadership skills, cooking and nutrition, traditional foodways, and community outreach through special projects, including the installation of low-cost home garden beds for neighbors interested in growing their own food.  Roots Tree Crew interns are trained as Pennsylvania Horticultural Society Tree Tenders and work alongside horticulturists to plant in the neighborhood, lead community science activities and tree tours, and canvass neighbors to support residents in planting and caring for new trees. Serving all youth; specially in the Southwest, West areas.

Serving LGBTQIA youth, in or are aging out of foster care, justice impacted (juvenile justice or criminal justice); citywide.

For 12-13 year olds we have a 6 week workshop series that they participate in with peers to explore careers of interest, learn about financial responsibility and get ready for their high school pathway. As apprentices, the program provides rising 1st through 3rd grade scholars with literacy intervention and an affirming space that celebrates their culture and racial identity. Scholars also participate in trips, enrichment activities, and project-based learning.  Serving all youth.

records.Name: Children's Hospital of Philadelphia (CHOP)
records.Description: CHOP Career Path is a supported employment program for youth with disabilities and/or chronic illnesses. Serving youth with disabilities, chronically ill, pregnant or parenting, in or are aging out of foster care, justice impacted (juvenile justice or criminal justice); citywide, specially in the South, Southwest areas.

records.Name: Community College of Philadelphia
records.Description:
Community College of Philadelphia 's Advanced Manufacturing Summer Bootcamps are summer extension programs for our two School-to-Work Programs for Philadelphia HIgh School students, our PIpeline to Advanced Manufacturing Careers Program (Ben Franklin, Bartram, and Furness High Schools) and our Welding Pathway Program, featuring our Industrial Welding Pre-Apprenticeship Program (Welding students at Randolph, Ben Franklin, and Mastbaum High Schools).,a0xDL0000047HtwYAE
These summer project-based learning programs will enhance the Pipeline to Advanced Manufacturing Careers Program and the Welding Pathway Program by providing hands-on learning experiences combined with direct interactions with employers that will support students in their learning pathway. records.Name: Guiding Stars An Anthony C Richardson Lee Foundation
records.Description: Guiding Stars partners with several grassroots organizations that address issues of the inner city youth. The organization 's C2L-PHL programs focus on professionalism while providing real-life work experience in the communities we live in. Youth in the program range from ages 12-24 and are encouraged to apply if they reside in the Northwest Section of Philadelphia. Serving youth with disabilities, chronically ill, pregnant or parenting, in or are aging out of foster care; specially in the Germantown, Olney/Oak Lane, Roxborough/Manayunk areas.

records.Name: Harlem Lacrosse - Philadelphia
records.Description: Harlem Lacrosse Summer Camp gives HL students the opportunity to build on the athletic, academic, and SEL skills that they learn during the school year. Serving all youth; specially in the Olney/Oak Lane area.

records.Name: Heights - Carver High School
records.Description: This Heights programs includes two types of programs. The Middle Grades Bridge is intended for students who are rising 7th and rising 8th graders. This program takes place at the same time and place as the 9th grade bridge summer program. 9th Grade Summer Bridge is a 5-week summer program that offers incoming 9th-grade students Math, Science, and English classes. Additionally, it includes college campus tours, an empowerment conference, field trips, various electives, and a range of enriching activities.

records.Name: Heights - Community Partnership School
records.Description: The Academy program provides rigorous learning opportunities to high-achieving students attending top-performing independent schools in Philadelphia. The program begins our long-term relationship with scholars as rising 5th-8th graders through the summer and school year programs. The program develops scholars? critical thinking, writing, and reading skills through our math, science, ELA, electives, and advisory courses. The program encourages scholars to be curious learners and stretch their academic abilities in the Academy program. Partner schools are Penn Charter, Baldwin, Agnes Irwin, Haverford, Friends? Central, Friends? Select, Episcopal, Holy Child of Rosemont, St. Peter?s, Community Partnership School, and selective charter and parochial schools.

records.Name: Heights - Temple University
records.Description: This Heights Program includes the Summer Institute Program, The Advanced Senior Year (ASY) Program, a Dual Enrollment Program with Temple or Temple Fox School of Business, the Summer Business and Entrepreneurship Program, the Temple + Heights STEM Research Program, the ACS Project SEED Lab Research Program, BEAM (Biomedical &Life Science Foundations Program), and, the Healthcare Foundations Summer.

records.Name: Heights - University of Pennsylvania
records.Description: This Heights program includes two types of programs. BLI Computer Science Academy, a 6-week summer Computer Science enrichment program for current 8th-11th graders (rising 9th-12th). Introductory &Intermediate Java classes available. Includes classes, projects, &special panels/ events. Prepares students for our school-year BLI AP Computer Science A class. The Wharton Pre-baccalaureate Program offers a rigorous academic experience for outstanding high school juniors and seniors. Participants have the chance to take credit-bearing courses covering various aspects of Wharton 's business curriculum.

records.Name: Kensington Soccer Club
records.Description: The KSC Summer Jumpstart program aims to familiarize teenagers with the responsibilities of employment. Participants will gain essential skills in professionalism and job readiness while assisting in basic soccer training for youth. The program extends soccer opportunities to local summer camps, enriching the community through sports and mentorship. Serving all youth; specially in the Center City, Germantown, North, Northeast, Kensington areas.

records.Name: Lenfest Center for Community Workforce Partnerships (LCCWP)
records.Description: Lenfest Center for Community Workforce Partnership (LCCWP) is a waged-based provider partner who connect young people to summer opportunities within our network of worksites. The program includes placement in a professional work environment, pre-employment training, and ongoing learning opportunities for reflection. The program encourages applications from young peoples between the ages of 14-24 years old, with limited-to-no work experience, who are motivated to learn and contribute meaningfully to a community worksite agency. Serving all youth; citywide, specially in the North area.

records.Name: LNESC
records.Description: LNESC C2L-PHL Program is designed to give youth their first work experiences. The program offers work opportunities in several areas including childcare, summer camps, maintenance, doctors offices, and animal care. It offers opportunities that provide youth with 21st Century Skills that are transferable across several industries. Serving low-Income, first generation youth; specially in the Kensington, Northeast, North areas.

records.Name: Mural Arts Philadelphia - 8th Street
records.Description: Every summer, Mural Arts provides a paid career-exposure learning program to Philadelphia-based youth aged 14-21. This six-week intensive program introduces youth participants to hands-on work readiness experiences in what it takes to be a working artist. Serving all youth; citywide.

records.Name: Philadelphia Youth Network
records.Description: For many young people, the introduction to the world of work can set the tone for the rest of their lives. WorkReady Boost offers young people the chance to work in many different career fields in order to develop the critical skills necessary to grow in an increasingly competitive economy. Serving all youth; citywide.

records.Name: Rock to the Future - Washington Ln
records.Description: Rock to the Future 's Summer Music Experiences offer participating students (ages 12-18) creative skill and career development opportunities. Interested in learning an instrument, music production, and graphic design? Want to attend educational workshops and perform live at our end of summer showcases? Join us at either one of our locations in Germantown or Kensington! Serving all youth; citywide.

records.Name: Rock to the Future -Emerald St
records.Description: Rock to the Future 's Summer Music Experiences offer participating students (ages 12-18) creative skill and career development opportunities. Interested in learning an instrument, music production, and graphic design? Want to attend educational workshops and perform live at our end of summer showcases? Join us at either one of our locations in Germantown or Kensington! Serving all youth; citywide.

records.Name: School District of Philadelphia - Start UP EDU
records.Description: Students will gain an entrepreneurial mindset in this five-week program and the skills needed to start a business by learning the integral skills needed when becoming an entrepreneur. Students will need a Chromebook for this program. Students will learn concepts such as presentation skills, targeting a market, finances, budgeting, entrepreneurship skills and more! Serving all youth; citywide.

records.Name: SEAMAAC, Inc. - Academy at Palumbo
records.Description: SEAMAAC offers a vibrant summer program, offering Hip Hop Arts studios in Dance, Music Production, Photography and Video Production.  Participants have the opportunity to create original music, beats, dance choreography, videos and photographic projects and develop their portfolios during the 6-week C2L Summer Program.  No prior experience in our Hip Hop Arts studios is required - all are welcomed. Serving all youth; citywide.

records.Name: Somerset Academy Early Learning Center
records.Description: Somerset Academy offers youth the opportunity to gain working skills in the area of early childhood education Serving all youth, youth with disabilities; citywide, specially in the Center City, North, Kensington areas.

records.Name: Sunrise of Philadelphia
records.Description: At Sunrise of Philadelphia, youth will learn how their interests relate to choosing a career. Youth will discover and research a career path and what it takes for them to get there. Youth will be exposed to different career paths and choices through trips, discussions, facilitation and their own research. Serving all youth; citywide, specially in the South, West, Southwest areas.

records.Name: The Niche Clinic - Counter Culture
records.Description: At the Niche Clinic, youth will learn about money while earning money. The program offers financial literacy infused across a wide variety of career-connected learning opportunities, including: weight-lifting, boxing, botany/green house, chemistry, debate team, entrepreneurship and small business creations, classic internships and so much more. Participants (and their parents) make their own unique schedule for the summer. Serving all youth, youth with disabilities or justice impacted; specially in the Southwest, West, Germantown, Northeast, Olney/Oak Lane areas.

records.Name: The School District of Philadelphia -Career Prep
records.Description: The CareerPrep Education Center (440) Internship Program will provide students in rising grades 10 - 12 with paid workplace experiences at the SDP Education Center (440) for six (6) weeks.  As a CareerPrep Intern, students will: meet ACT 158 Requirements (pathway 5), gain real-world experiences, exposure to career opportunities in the education industry, and develop a deeper understanding of how schools are connected to economic success. Serving all youth

records.Name: The School District of Philadelphia -CTE
records.Description: The School District of Philadelphia, through the Office of Career &Technical Education (CTE), is offering summer employment and enrichment opportunities for School District of Philadelphia CTE students. This program is an extension of the CTE curriculum. Students in this program will gain valuable work experience and develop practical skills that can be used in their future careers. Serving all School District of Philadelphia Career Technical Education students.

records.Name: The U School Inc.
records.Description: The U School 's summer program focuses on sustainable entrepreneurship, food production &processing, and green career (food, ag natural resources/environmental education) pathway exploration. Serving all youth; specially in the North area.

records.Name: The Village of Arts and Humanities
records.Description: The Village of Arts and Humanities 'award-winning programs offer excellent free arts education and paid creative opportunities to youth. Taught by top working artists, the organization 's programs support young people to enter the workforce and postsecondary education as creative problem solvers and social innovators. This includes Urban Farming, Fashion Design, Clay +  3D sculpture, Dance, Music Production and a variety of other creative studio internships.  Serving all youth; citywide, specially in the North area.

records.Name: The Workshop School
records.Description: The Workshop School WorkReady Summer programs are specifically targeted towards current Workshop School students.  The organization 's summer programs are an extension and expansion of work that students participate in during the academic year.  Summer program opportunities are limited to Workshop School students only.  Serving youth already involved with the Workshop School; citywide, specially in the West, Southwest areas.

records.Name: University of Pennsylvania - Vice Provost for Student Engagement Division (VPSE)
records.Description: The VPSE Summer 2024 CCL program will include skill development training, career exploration, and work-readiness programming that prepares youth for unsubsidized employment through job readiness training, career exposure, and subsidized internships. Participants will, through one of three program modules, PennRSSA, SMP, or the VPSE Stem Program, be provided with multidisciplinary college access, workforce development, and career readiness summer programming including content from all 12 Schools at Penn: Annenberg School for Communication, Arts and Sciences, Dental Medicine, Weitzman School of Design, Engineering and Applied Science, Graduate School of Education, Carey Law School, Nursing, Perelman School of Medicine, Social Policy and Practice, Veterinary Medicine, and the Wharton School of Business.  The VPSE Summer 2024 CCL Program will also increase student access to high-quality learning experiences through engaging, high-caliber academic enrichment, exposure to varied careers, skill development, internship capstone opportunities, and individualized support with college and employment application processes. Serving all youth; citywide.

records.Name: Urban Affairs Coalition
records.Description: Urban Affairs Coalition 's program connects youth with career immersion opportunities in zip codes throughout the city of Philadelphia. In addition to direct career immersion, youth will attend workshops teaching soft skills and financial literacy. In addition, they will be introduced to various career fields to increase their knowledge of career options. Serving all youth; citywide.

records.Name: VestedIn - WesGold Fellows
records.Description: WesGold Fellows is a yearlong fellowship for high school students that kicks off with an intensive paid 8-week summer internship that focuses on real estate, financial literacy, and entrepreneurship. During this time, Fellows develop their finance, professionalism, public speaking, networking, and college and career planning skills. The organization 's mission is to contribute to the development of the next generation of leaders who will engage, impact, and grow our economy. Serving all youth citywide.

records.Name: We Love Philly
records.Description: Young people will work in various positions within the We Love Philly Digital Marketing Agency in create content to ensure their voices are heard with the upcoming SemiQuincentennial. Students will be earning Industry Recognized Credentials and cementing a position in our Pre Apprenticeship Program if they wish to continue in the fall. Serving all youth; citywide.
